text: Bolshekyzylbayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Alegazovsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 451 as of 2010. There are 9 streets. == Geography == It is located 15 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye, 5 km from Alegazovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Bolshekyzylbayevo
